  "texts": [
    "Yet this sentence was marked as medium harm severity (0.637) for sexually explicit content.",
    "We believe that this mistake arose from the word kerhâne in the Ottoman sentence.",
    "In Modern Turkish, kerhâne, refers exclusively to a place of sex work.",
    "However in OT it refers to a place of work more generally.",
    "Moreover, this example deals with a compound noun temürcü kerhânesi where temürcü means blacksmith, which is why it is translated into English as blacksmith's workshop."
  ],
